Package: jocf
Title: Joint Ordered Correlation Forest
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Riccardo", "Di Francesco", email = "TODO@email.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Estimates conditional choice probabilities and classifications
    for ordered discrete outcomes using a single random forest with a joint
    splitting criterion that minimises average estimation error across all
    classes simultaneously.  In contrast to the published 'ocf' package,
    which grows M separate forests, 'jocf' grows one forest whose splitting
    rule is equivalent to minimising total CART Gini impurity (Proposition 1
    in the package vignette).  The single-forest structure enables a
    majority-vote classifier not available to multi-forest approaches.
